# PixelVault — Cursor IDE Rules

You are working on PixelVault, a multi-model AI image/video generation + permanent archive platform.

## Stack
Next.js 16 (App Router + Turbopack) · TypeScript · Clerk · Prisma 7 + PostgreSQL (Neon) · Cloudflare R2 · next-intl (en/ja/zh)

## Critical Architecture Rules

### Data Flow (NEVER violate)
```
constants → types (Zod) → services → hooks → components
```
- Constants: `src/constants/` — all config, enums, routes. Check here FIRST before adding new values.
- Types: `src/types/index.ts` — Zod schemas + inferred TypeScript types. NEVER use `any` or `as` assertions.
- Services: `src/services/` — server-only business logic. Must `import 'server-only'` at top.
- Hooks: `src/hooks/` — client-side state. All API calls go through `src/lib/api-client.ts`.
- Components: `src/components/business/` (stateful) | `src/components/ui/` (stateless shadcn).

### API Routes (`src/app/api/`)
Every route does exactly 3 things:
1. `const { userId } = await auth()` — Clerk auth check
2. `Schema.safeParse(body)` — Zod validation
3. `await someService(...)` — delegate to service layer

NO business logic in routes. NO database queries in routes.

### AI Provider System
- 7 adapters in `src/services/providers/`: huggingface, gemini, openai, fal, replicate, novelai, volcengine
- All implement `ProviderAdapter` interface from `src/services/providers/types.ts`
- Registry in `src/services/providers/registry.ts` — use `getProviderAdapter(adapterType)`
- Models defined in `src/constants/models.ts` (enum `AI_MODELS`)
- Adapter types in `src/constants/providers.ts` (enum `AI_ADAPTER_TYPES`)

### Card/Recipe System
- Cards: character, background, style, model — each in `src/services/<type>-card.service.ts`
- Recipe compilation: `src/services/recipe-compiler.service.ts` — fuses cards into a single prompt
- Two compilation modes: LLM fusion (primary) → template fallback

### Resilience Utilities (use these)
- `src/lib/with-retry.ts` — wrap external API calls with exponential backoff
- `src/lib/circuit-breaker.ts` — per-provider circuit breaker
- `src/lib/prompt-guard.ts` — validate prompts before sending to AI
- `src/lib/llm-output-validator.ts` — validate LLM responses
- `src/lib/logger.ts` — structured logging (NEVER use console.log in services)

### i18n
- 3 locale files: `src/messages/{en,ja,zh}.json` — ALL THREE must stay in sync
- Use `useTranslations('Namespace')` in components
- NEVER hardcode user-facing strings

## Forbidden Patterns
- `any` type — use Zod schema + `z.infer<>`
- `fetch()` in components — use `src/lib/api-client.ts`
- `console.log` in services — use `src/lib/logger.ts`
- Tailwind arbitrary values like `w-[347px]` — extend config instead
- Magic numbers/strings — use `src/constants/`
- `as` type assertions — derive types from Zod schemas
- Pure white `#fff` background — use `#faf9f5`
- Blue-purple gradients, neon colors, heavy shadows

## Design Language
- Background: `#faf9f5` · Text: `#141413` · Accent: `#d97757`
- Fonts: Space Grotesk (headings) + Lora (body)
- Motion: fade-in + translate-up, 300-600ms ease-out only

## Common Mistakes to Avoid
1. Adding a new model without updating ALL of: `AI_MODELS` enum, model config, i18n (3 files), provider adapter
2. Creating a service without `import 'server-only'` at top
3. Putting business logic in API routes instead of service layer
4. Forgetting to update all 3 i18n files when adding UI text
5. Using `z.parse()` (throws) in API routes — use `z.safeParse()` instead
6. Not validating prompt length — add `.max(4000)` on prompt fields
